Subject: [PATCH v10 17/21] soc-camera: switch I2C subdevice drivers to use v4l2-clk
Date: Tue, 11 Jun 2013 10:23:44 +0200
Message-Id: <1370939028-8352-18-git-send-email-g.liakhovetski@gmx.de>
In-Reply-To: <1370939028-8352-1-git-send-email-g.liakhovetski@gmx.de>
References: <1370939028-8352-1-git-send-email-g.liakhovetski@gmx.de>
Sender: linux-media-owner@vger.kernel.org
List-ID: <linux-media.vger.kernel.org>

Instead of centrally enabling and disabling subdevice master clocks in
soc-camera core, let subdevice drivers do that themselves, using the
V4L2 clock API and soc-camera convenience wrappers.

Signed-off-by: Guennadi Liakhovetski <g.liakhovetski@gmx.de>
